{
  "texts": [
    "Risky driving behaviors, noted in 13% of crashes, are less significant but still important.",
    "These behaviors, possibly related to the age of the driver (e.g., teenagers and females), include unsafe maneuvers like lane changing or speeding to bypass slower traffic.",
    "Such actions not only increase crash risk but also disrupt traffic flow.",
    "Given the high proportion of crashes linked to traffic congestion, addressing this issue is vital for enhancing safety in Segment 1.",
    "Prioritizing congestion management strategies, such as implementing ramp metering to regulate flow and improving road infrastructure, is essential."
  ]
}